violinplot
=============

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

df = sns.load_dataset("iris")

sns.violinplot(data=df, x="species", y="sepal_length")
plt.show()



sns.violinplot(data=df, x="species", y="sepal_length", inner="quartile")

Options:

"box" → mini boxplot
"quartile" → lines for Q1, median, Q3
"point" → points
None → nothing inside


sns.violinplot(data=df, x="species", y="sepal_length", hue="species")


catplot
===========

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

df = sns.load_dataset("iris")

sns.catplot(data=df, x="species", y="sepal_length", kind="box")
plt.show()




Most Important Parameter → kind
This decides which plot you want
box
violin
bar
strip
swarm


sns.catplot(data=df, x="species", y="sepal_length", kind="violin")
sns.catplot(data=df, x="species", y="sepal_length", kind="bar")

sns.catplot(
    data=df,
    x="species",
    y="sepal_length",
    kind="box",
    col="species"
)

sns.catplot(
    data=df,
    x="species",
    y="sepal_length",
    kind="box",
    row="species"
)
